## Part 3: Auto-Sharpening

For medium and high tier days (NOT tail days), the mask die and jitter level are determined by the day’s **current zone**, not the zone it was in when revealed.

This means a medium-tier day that was in zone D (d8 mask) when first revealed will have a d10 mask when it reaches zone C, d12 at zone B, and d20 at zone A. The tier flag doesn’t change — still medium — but forecast reliability improves as the day approaches.

### Seeding for stability

The mask roll must be deterministic so the forecast doesn’t flicker between views. Seed on `(serial, zone, worldSeed, 'mask')`. When a day crosses a zone boundary, it gets a fresh roll at the new (better) odds. Within a zone, the result is stable.

The jitter seed should work similarly: `(serial, zone, worldSeed, 'jitter')`.

