## Part 12: Seeded Deterministic Rolls

All forecast lens rolls must be deterministic per `(serial, zone, purpose)` so the forecast doesn’t flicker between views. Use the existing world seed as the base.

When a day crosses a zone boundary (auto-sharpening), the zone component of the seed changes, producing a fresh roll at the new odds. This is intentional — it’s the forecast “updating” at natural breakpoints.

Suggested seed structure:

```typescript
function _forecastSeed(serial: number, zone: string, purpose: string): number {
  // Combine with existing world seed
  return hash(worldSeed, serial, zone, purpose);
}
```

Where `purpose` is one of: `'mask'`, `'jitter-direction-wind'`, `'jitter-direction-precip'`, `'jitter-direction-temp'`, `'mask-snap'`.

