## Part 13: Edge Cases

1. **First day of forecast window with no previous record**: Use `rec.base` (seasonal baseline) as regression target instead of `prevRec.final`.
1. **DC 25 medium check**: All 10 days are medium. No visible tail (tail would be days 11-13, beyond display cap). Tail flags may still be planted internally but never rendered.
1. **Multiple checks on overlapping windows**: Each check may upgrade some days. The quality rank comparison handles this — a new DC 15 check can’t downgrade days that already have DC 20 medium quality.
1. **Location change**: Existing reveals are per-location (already implemented). The forecast lens reads the location-specific reveal bucket. Changing location doesn’t invalidate old reveals at the old location; they just stop being displayed when the weather location changes.
1. **Day 1 with no previous day record**: Fallback to `rec.base` as regression target. This should only happen on the very first day of a campaign or after a full weather reset.
1. **Planar overlay decomposition unavailable**: If `rec.overlay` is not present (legacy records generated before this feature), treat the entire delta as natural. No planar decomposition, full regression. This is the safe fallback.